# Projocalypse plan ↔ board sync

Read [doc/MONOREPO.md](../../doc/MONOREPO.md). Plan markdown is the **master** backlog; the embedded board is the sprint surface.

## Plan item format

```markdown
- [ ] pm:PM-043 COPPA consent gate <!-- pm:section=Sprint pm:priority=high -->
- [x] pm:PM-042 Magic link flow <!-- pm:section=Done -->
```

- Every trackable item needs a **stable `pm:PM-###` id** (unique across all plan files for the package).
- Headings set default section; `<!-- pm:section=... -->` overrides.
- Mark `[x]` when work is **done**; move section to `Done` (or package `doneSection` from `.projocalypse/workspace.json`).

## After editing plan files

From host repo root, for the affected `--package` (from `.projocalypse/workspace.json`):

```bash
pnpm pm:plan --package <name>
pnpm pm:gap --package <name>
pnpm pm:sync --package <name>
```

Commit `.projocalypse/pending/*.json` when pending upserts change so CI and embed import stay current.

## When shipping a feature

1. Complete the board task (or confirm it in gap output).
2. Update plan: `[x]` + `pm:section=Done` for that `pm:ID`.
3. Run gap again; fix `STATUS_MISMATCH` and `SECTION_DRIFT`.
4. Export board snapshot if the host app writes `.projocalypse/board/` (needed for accurate gap).

## Gap codes (fix before merge when blocking)

| Code | Action |
|------|--------|
| `MISSING_ON_BOARD` | Run `pm:sync`; reload embed to import pending |
| `STATUS_MISMATCH` | Align checkbox vs task `completed` (plan usually wins for Done) |
| `SECTION_DRIFT` | Move task column or update `pm:section` metadata |
| `MISSING_FROM_PLAN` | Remove orphan board task or restore plan line |
| `NO_LINK` | Link host entity `projocalypseProjectId` in `.projocalypse/links/` |

## Do not

- Add duplicate `pm:PM-###` ids across files.
- Use external PM tools for in-repo sprint items registered in `workspace.json`.
- Full-DB Projocalypse import on a shared origin without user confirmation.

Use skill **`projocalypse-plan-sync`** for full agent workflow. Initial embed setup: **`projocalypse-sprint-setup`**.
